# FastAPI Guidance

## Project Context

- FastAPI version: {{ fastapi_version | default("detected by Akira") }}
- Async stack: {{ async_stack | default("detected from database and imports") }}
- Router style: {{ router_style | default("APIRouter per feature or domain") }}

## Endpoint Shape

- Define routes on `APIRouter`, then include routers in the application factory
  or main app module.
- Use `response_model` for successful JSON responses.
- Use `status` constants instead of raw status integers.
- Keep route functions thin: validate input, call service/domain code, and
  translate results into API responses.
- Put shared concerns such as auth, database sessions, and pagination in
  `Depends()` dependencies.

{% if uses_pydantic_v2 | default(true) %}
## Pydantic v2

- Use `model_validate()` when converting ORM or domain objects to schemas.
- Use `model_dump()` when passing request payloads into domain constructors.
- Keep request and response models separate when fields differ.
{% endif %}

## Pydantic v2 Models

- Separate request models from response models when the fields differ; do not
  reuse ORM models as API schemas.
- Use `model_validate(obj)` to construct a Pydantic model from a dict or ORM
  object. Use `model_dump()` to convert back. The v1 `.from_orm()` and
  `.dict()` methods are removed.
- Use `model_config = ConfigDict(from_attributes=True)` on response models
  that are constructed from ORM objects.
- Field validators use `@field_validator("field_name")` with `@classmethod`.
  The v1 `@validator` decorator is removed.
- `Annotated[str, Field(min_length=1)]` is the canonical style for constrained
  fields.
- Avoid `Optional[X]` on request body fields that are truly required; use
  `X | None = None` only when the field is intentionally nullable.

{% if is_async_app | default(false) %}
## Async Rules

- Keep async endpoints non-blocking.
- Await database, HTTP, queue, and storage calls.
- Move CPU-heavy work to a task runner or sync helper outside the request path.
- Do not call sync SQLAlchemy sessions from async endpoints.
{% endif %}

